Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:01:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an hour late. I'm going to pass the, I just thought some people might put this together.\NIt sounds sort of academically. It starts with a syllabus, and then it goes on to a synopsis.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.79,0:01:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We could pass these out. A syllabus and a synopsis. It tells us what we're going to be talking about today,\Nwhich I have the slightest idea, but it looks good on paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.37,0:01:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It features the academic people. Well, I did give a conference a week or two ago,\Nand a lot of people get continuing education credits, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.48,0:02:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If any of you need continuing education credits, I have certificates of education here, good, for three credits.\NToday will certainly be at least three credits. So anybody who needs any, I have these here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.41,0:02:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all signed, and we'll just put the date, and the name of the presentation is on the syllabus.\NAnd so those who would like, you know, continuing education academic credits, we officially have them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.31,0:02:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Close for five minutes early. I just want to make sure we're close for five minutes early.\NAnd if we run out of them, we'll get some more made.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.22,0:02:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, what we do is, let's see what the name of it would be.\NWe have Commissioner Ashley's, which is, I feel like it's over 470, 472, 475, 480, 478, 479, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 770 before, but I did resist.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.46,0:03:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a very exciting audience to speak to.\NWell, what we always do is calibrate the level of consciousness of the audience before and after the presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.42,0:03:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And historically, the level of consciousness of the audience usually jumps considerably.\NI mean, a group like this will jump considerably.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And the average group will jump probably about 10 points.\NAnd as we said in the book, Power Versus Force,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.12,0:03:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of the average person increases by five points in a lifetime.\NSo if you can knock off 10 points in one lecture, that's two lifetimes right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.66,0:03:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's two times you won't have to come back.\NSo anyway, I just thought that was good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.28,0:04:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have most luxurious accommodations here.\NAnd we were greeted in the most impressive airport parking lot I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.31,0:04:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In my life.\NIt went on for miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.51,0:04:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We traveled.\NShe had a compass with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.51,0:04:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It was phenomenal, I thought.\NIt took great courage, great courage and stamina to, brave that to come and find us and bring us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.51,0:04:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we are in California.\NNow, you see, we have to set up for transparency and the transparency of course is sitting home on my desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.50,0:04:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.79,0:04:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.87,0:04:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.95,0:04:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.03,0:04:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.31,0:04:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.43,0:04:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.25,0:04:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, today we will just have to speak from truth and that will have to do it.\NAnd the other thing we'll do that's different in this lecture is we'll stay right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.13,0:05:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll stay right now at all times.\NAnd I want you to notice that we will not let the past catch up with us or the future elude us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.83,0:05:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Because most people spend all their time trying to catch the past, the future before it escapes them.\Nand holding off the past so it won't catch up with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.41,0:05:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only safe place to be at any time is right now.\NAnd so throughout this lecture we'll say right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.74,0:05:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So everybody will be safe from the past and safe from the future.\NAnd the reason for saying that is because everyone looks to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.17,0:05:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, where is enlightenment and when is it going to happen?\NAnd everybody looks into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.71,0:05:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Or they look into the past.\NThey say it's either my karma from the past
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.63,0:05:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or it's something that I will evolve into sometime in the future\Nor some future lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.30,0:06:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fact is it's found in the immediate moment of now,\Nin the split second, in the split second between two thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.34,0:06:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which is what the Buddha said.\NAnd he was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.94,0:06:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in the same place he said it was.\NIn fact, it was still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.96,0:06:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It never moved in all these thousands of years.\NIt's right here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.91,0:06:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And how to stay on the edge of now is partly what we'll be talking about today.\NSo the syllabus says that we will be talking about who the speaker is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.80,0:06:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and various subjects.\NWe will cover the levels of consciousness and their inference.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.73,0:06:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be talking about the different situations,\Nbetween linear and non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.25,0:06:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So to make everything that I say simple,\Nwe'll start out from the most difficult and obscure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.89,0:07:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That will make the rest simple.\NAnd that is that we have two ways of experiencing reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.33,0:07:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,One is in the linear Newtonian paradigm of reality,\Nwhich has to do with form, has to do with structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.29,0:07:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And the linear linearism,\Nlinear reality is discreditable in terms of advanced theoretical math and physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.93,0:07:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially of the differential calculus.\NBut a lot of data falls outside the realm of the predictable mathematically.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.85,0:07:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It falls outside the expected paradigm of science.\NAnd our society is primarily oriented to the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.03,0:07:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our society in America, the caliber is extremely high,\Nand indicates that it's the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:07:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and indicates that it's the intellect,\Nand indicates that it's the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.15,0:08:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that we worship as God.\NScience is the, it's taken over the point,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.49,0:08:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the one that's taken by religion.\NSo when we look for answers, we look to the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.27,0:08:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and we look for science to come up with the answers.\NThe only difficulty with science is that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.08,0:08:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in our level of consciousness, as you can see,\Nwe have our levels of consciousness here,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.98,0:08:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a map of consciousness where everybody can just refer to it if they want.\NBut the reason the intellect calibrates in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.39,0:08:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,well,\Nspiritual truth in reality, you know, the reality of spiritual truth really commences formally around 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.47,0:08:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,500 is the level of love, 540 is unconditional love.\NSo the realm of science then takes us up really to 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.74,0:09:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If we calibrate 499, we see Einstein, Freud, Sir Isaac Newton,\Nall the great scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All the great geniuses of old time calibrate around 499.\N500 is the level of the heart, 500 is the opening of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.65,0:09:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,500 is the, really the, taking over of the non-linear dimension.\NFrom 500 and up we're talking about qualities that are powerful qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.92,0:09:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that cannot be measured.\NLove, meaning, significance, motivation, all the things that run human beings,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.94,0:09:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,are in the non-linear, non-measurable domain,\Nand therefore not within the realm of science, not describable, not measurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.02,0:09:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the radical materialist, reductionist materialism,\Nstates that unless a thing can be weighed or measured,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.00,0:10:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then it has no reality.\NIt's only a tautology, that's a popular philosophic system that says you can't measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.53,0:10:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tautology,\Nand a philosophic system that says you can't measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.09,0:10:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tautology, and a philosophic system that says you can't measure it.\Nit's a tautology, and a philosophic system that says you can't measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.55,0:10:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tautology, and a philosophical system, but not a reality.\NWell, today we're going to say the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.36,0:10:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we're going to say that the measurable is a perceptual construct,\Nand that what's real is that which cannot be measured.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.86,0:10:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that make human life human, none of them are measurable.\NAlthough we talk in language, and verbalize, and move about in a physical material world,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.62,0:10:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,human existence is really lived on the level\Nof the non-linear. From moment to moment, although you may be observing a linear reality
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.78,0:11:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,such as tables and chairs or numbers or articles in a grocery store, at every instant you're\Nreally coming out of an invisible space of your own existence which has no form whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when you decide to vote, you just, out of your right side of your brain, you pick\Nthis one. Then suddenly the left side comes in and says, the reason I picked this one
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.82,0:11:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is this. All that is an afterthought. You didn't pick it for that reason at all. You\Ndon't even know why you picked what you picked because it has to do with 10 million variables
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.36,0:11:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time and throughout all of this existence and all the input of this\Nentire lifetime and all of the subtleties and interactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.29,0:11:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So.\NSo complex that no computer could possibly calculate it. So our real existence then,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.42,0:12:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,although we deal with form, we deal with form from a space of non-form, the non-linear dimension\Nof reality. And spiritual work then is concerned with the non-dimensional, the non-dimensional
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.25,0:12:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,non-measurable. So of course what we did in the book, what we did in Power vs. Force is\Nmeasure the immeasurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.82,0:12:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what was the purpose of that? The purpose of that was to try to make the obvious comprehensible.\NBecause the people who are in left brain and into the world of science and logic and calibrate,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.35,0:12:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say in the 400s or below, spiritual reality is not a real reality to them. And\Nthe scientific people would like to say this is all fantasy, etc. But it's not. It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.24,0:12:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not. It's not.\NIt's not. It's not. It's not. It is not. It's not. It is not. It's not. So what we needed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.33,0:12:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,was a means of crossing over from Newtonian paradigm of reality, measurable, scientific,\Nlogical, sequential world of existence to the non-linear world of spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.90,0:13:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and a way of making the non-spiritual world comprehensible to the intellect. So the\Nwhole purpose of the map of consciousness, which is on the back of page 1, is to make
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.88,0:13:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the non-life understand the idea of spiritual reality as something that is not absolutely\Nmeaning in topic. So the purpose of the map of consciousness is to make the non-life stream,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.92,0:13:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,transition from the nonlinear to the linear comprehensible so that even the scientific\Nskeptic can look at it and say huh you mean to tell me there is an actual objective means
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.12,0:13:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you know verifying the existence of a nonlinear domain not only that but calibrating its low\Nrelative energy its relative power so when we did the levels of consciousness we started out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.89,0:14:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from one to a thousand one to a thousand and then we found this out the scale came about empirically\Nwe said if the existence is one existence is one logarithmic scale what would be the highest number
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.10,0:14:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,ever achieved by any living being and instead of thousand I thought well that's pretty neat\None to a thousand that's very cooperative so then we went back and we asked
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.86,0:14:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we found out that that which is true makes you go strong with kinesiology and that which\Nis false makes you go weak and what was the number of that and we came up with 200 so the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.49,0:14:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,most crucial thing about the map of consciousness is that anything under 200 makes you go weak and\Nanything over 200 makes you go strong so the exciting thing was that kinesiology differentiated
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.74,0:14:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood that was the most significant finding and when I studied\Nkinesiology I attended lectures by John Diamond who wrote your body doesn't lie and he's a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.68,0:15:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful teacher he's a psychiatrist and he's in New York and John Diamond had picked up the\Nkinesiologic technique from George Goodhart chiropractor I think in Detroit who had worked
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.17,0:15:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,on muscle testing and then Diamond took it to a different level he took it to the level where he\Ndemonstrated that he was able to do a lot of things and he was able to do a lot of things
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.13,0:15:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,attitudes attitudes and feelings affected the kinetic response and then I just took it some\Ndimensions further and discovered that one could calibrate all the levels of the fields of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.42,0:15:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness and that a peculiar thing was happening that the kinesiologic response was\Nnot a local physical response that has had been resumed that was instead a non-specific
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.47,0:15:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal response of the\Nof consciousness itself, that when we ask somebody a question with kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.18,0:16:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,what is answering, is consciousness itself, not the person. So the response\Nbypasses the personality of both the questioner and the test subject, and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.38,0:16:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,instead you're tapping into some universal, all-present, ever-present\Nenergy field beyond all of time, which we call consciousness. And the discovery was
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.90,0:16:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that anything and everything that had ever happened, anywhere in time or\Nhistory, any time in time or space, no matter how small, every single thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.11,0:16:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling, movement, every action, by anything or anyone, anywhere in the\Nuniverse, was recorded forever. That it is true, as Scripture says, that every hair on
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.16,0:17:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,your head should be counted.\NEvery single thing that occurs then leaves an indelible trace, and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.32,0:17:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is beyond time and space, so it's there forever. What Napoleon said,\Nthought, or felt, every moment of his life can be tracked back again. In the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.17,0:17:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the day of his death, we can find out what he had for breakfast.\NAlright, so this was rather mind-boggling, and I sort of sat on it for about five
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.62,0:17:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,years not knowing what to do with this.\NWe now had something that is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.92,0:17:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so mind-boggling that it takes practically a lifetime to get used to the\Nthought, that we now had the means unknown to mankind throughout all of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.57,0:17:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,history to discern truth from falsehood. Well, any student of human history,\Neven recent and remote, realizes that almost every event in history would have been
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.20,0:17:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,different had we given the capacity to know the truth from the falsehood. Jesus\NChrist says you don't know the truth from the falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.77,0:18:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He said watch out for the wolf in sheep's clothing, but he did not tell you how to tell\Nthe wolf in sheep's clothing. And until this very recent time, man has struggled, and I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.85,0:18:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,very, I'm writing a book right now called The Eye of the Eye, and in it I'm sort of\Ntracking sort of the tragedy almost of the evolution of mankind, and which throughout
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.84,0:18:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the histories has been beset by one plague after another, millions and millions slaughtered,\Nby disease, millions and millions slaughtered, by war, and even the most battle, recent battles
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.90,0:18:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in history, and you that are World War II buffs, every battle in history could\Ncould have been won if there was a capacity of knowing what the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.96,0:19:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,was up to, what the other side was up to. And if Hitler was going to come through\Nthe Ardon forest, which is a big surprise to veterans of World War II, it was
