Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.63,0:22:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,wiping out 70 million people and then that was followed by the flu epidemic of 1918 that knocked\Noff millions more and of course these were all survivors of the Black Plague which wiped out what
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.73,0:23:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,quarter or half of all of Europe after the hundred year war knocked out a good percentage of them you\Nsee yourself on the world event can't even get this far so all right so there it stood at 190
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.96,0:23:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly in 19 about 1986\Nconsciousness level of mankind suddenly jumped to 207 the most significant event in all of man's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.54,0:23:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,history unrecorded and unnoticed by anything or anyone the most profound and significant event in\Nthe history of all of mankind occurred in 1986 or so when the consciousness level of mankind shifted
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.34,0:23:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,from 190 which means endless disaster to 207 which means in the success all the difference in the\Nworld
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.80,0:24:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,just slightly below the water. Mankind has been struggling with his nose just below the water,\Ncoming up for a little air, and just barely making it. 207 means the universe and the world we live
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.68,0:24:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in now is a completely different energy field. At 190, negativity is socially acceptable. It's okay,\NDeutschland über alles. Sacrifice your sons and daughters to the grandeur of Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.96,0:24:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will conquer the world. At 190, that somehow captures people's imagination. At 207,\Nit sounds a little kooky. You say, yeah, uh huh, right, is this guy okay? 70 million people.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.08,0:24:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Germans didn't say, is this guy okay? They all saluted. Why? Because the predominant energy\Nfield at 190, negativity appeals to you. Militarism, smart uniforms, killing lower class
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.92,0:24:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,people is appealing.\NAt 207, it sounds pretty stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.62,0:25:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,At 407, where this crowd is, it's absurd. It's absurd. So mankind has not really\Nhad a chance to evolve, despite being at 190 we see the technologic advances in mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.79,0:25:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Our advances have been technologic, communications, electricity, modern wonders, airplanes and all\Nthose marvelous things. Marvelous 다음.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.46,0:25:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Marvelous, often known power.\NMarvelous, when you see material goods in Ukraine, when you see human capital goods in Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.18,0:25:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and so on so on.\NMarvelous times, hammering into its economic opportunities.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.44,0:25:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We have seen right forward, the company that our durantewoo, the techn reversal Sung\Na lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.82,0:25:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Marvelous but at a restaurant, and the way we have seen mankind, they do so much to its virtue.\NModern cultures don't give you the way you Thantない aids in dealing with Sarah Napol Hitomach .
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.98,0:25:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Marvelous, yes. Well, anyway. Conveniences. Marvelous conveniences.\NSo we see technologic progress over the centuries, but no real shift in the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.82,0:25:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No real shift in the heart of mankind.\NAnd suddenly we see a shift now, so that that which was once tolerable is no longer acceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.44,0:26:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,207 is a completely different playing field.\NSo at 190, North Korea can threaten South Korea with atomic weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.97,0:26:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and scare the bejesus out of them and throw the whole world into a third world war.\NWe came very close to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.60,0:26:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,At 207, it's rather unthinkable.\NAt 207, everybody looks at the opponents and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.74,0:26:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,listen, you better get together to solve this thing.\NAt 190, they gang up behind this opponent and they gang up behind this opponent
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.92,0:26:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they start a war.\NAt 190, that's acceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.80,0:26:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,At 207, everybody says,\Nlook, why don't you figure out a way? There must be a way out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.70,0:26:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see out of the Korean situation,\Nthen a resolution of a dilemma that had been there for 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.68,0:26:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The way that resolution came about was the awareness.\NYou see, the awareness that aggression just forms counter-aggression.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.93,0:26:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot possibly win with aggression\Nbecause the harder you push, the harder the other person pushes back.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.37,0:27:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You just precipitate attack.\NIt was inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.30,0:27:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And realizing that supporting the political position of their opponent,\Nthe opponent would then stop being warlike and welcome support
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.12,0:27:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you had an opening for resolution of difficulty,\Nwhich is exactly what did happen there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.28,0:27:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the leader of South Korea will be nominated for the Nobel Prize, etc.\NSo at 207, we see the resolution of things that would not have been possible in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.00,0:27:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw the dissolution of monolithic communism,\Nand that, again, was done without a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.98,0:27:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That was done without a shot.\NIt was not done by the Western world overpowering communism
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.28,0:27:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and bombing it into oblivion.\NIt was done by Gorbachev snapping his fingers and the whole thing fell apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.14,0:27:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,House of Cards dissolved without a single shot.\NGorbachev didn't shoot anybody, nor did he have any of his...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.84,0:28:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That was not popular in current communism, in current Russia, rather,\Nbecause even a corrupt government has certain benefits to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.00,0:28:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as we'll probably see now in Mexico.\NEven a corrupt government has certain benefits to certain parts of the populace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.31,0:28:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you change it, now everybody is wondering,\Nwhere is everything going to come from now?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.67,0:28:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everything now is thrown into a new paradigm of reality.\NSo we see that change of paradigm of reality shifting now even in politics in Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.95,0:28:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That which was corrupt was acceptable for some 70 years.\NIt's no longer acceptable, even to the people that participated in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.89,0:28:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see this general shift of consciousness prevailing throughout the world\Nand shifting public attitudes towards many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.67,0:28:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Capital punishment, which was a foregone conclusion, has come into question now.\NEven the Pope, God bless him,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.13,0:28:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,even the Pope has suddenly become very Christian and said,\Nbut Jesus said,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.23,0:29:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,proudly true, you did not kill your enemies,\Neven though it sounds justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.68,0:29:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have been very happy to see,\Nyou see, even Catholicism has come around to Christianity
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.04,0:29:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and supported Christ's teachings,\Nwhich it had not done for many, many centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.76,0:29:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And under the name of Christ,\Nyou could kill your enemies and execute them and hang them right and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.24,0:29:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it doesn't jive.\NSo we see this immense subtle shift in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.92,0:29:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and change in socialization,\Nattitudes towards many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.79,0:29:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The wisdom of capital punishment itself is now being brought into question.\NAnd in many countries it's illegal and going out of style.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.11,0:29:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the Pope says he thinks it's a poor idea.\NAnd that always puzzled me,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.67,0:29:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,how the Church could hold for capital punishment\Nconsidering what Jesus taught about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.59,0:30:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, those are the ambiguities of human consciousness.\NSo we see the difference between,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.10,0:30:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,between force and power,\Nwhat these things are bringing us to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.10,0:30:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The name of the book which I wrote was called\NPower vs. Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.29,0:30:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it compares the two different domains.\NThe lower consciousness levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.61,0:30:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of Newtonian logic, etc.\NThe world of form is the world of force,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.61,0:30:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quite a bit different than the world of power.\NIt has different rules, different laws,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.89,0:30:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,different ways of expressing itself,\Ndifferent consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.89,0:30:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What North and South Korea were looking at was,\Nonly a couple of years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.53,0:30:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of force.\NForce vs. force.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.79,0:30:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If one side used force, the other would use bigger force.\NSo what if it ended up as an atomic war, frankly,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.92,0:31:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,ballistic missiles and all.\NBecause force always results in counter force.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.46,0:31:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is true within the world of physics.\NIt's also true within the psychic domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.46,0:31:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But force results in counter force.\NNow, the characteristic of force is that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.00,0:31:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,force moves from here to there.\NForce moves from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.00,0:31:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And because it moves from here to there,\Nit consumes energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.04,0:31:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Force sooner or later runs out\Nbecause it runs out of its source of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.22,0:31:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can send only so many troops to the front\Nand then pretty soon your supply line goes down
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.22,0:31:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the spirit of the men goes down.\NAnd no matter how victorious your army may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.22,0:31:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only a matter of time before the Roman legions\Nwould reach defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.22,0:31:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They lasted longer than most.\NBut force is then consuming of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.76,0:32:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And force exhausts itself because in its expression\Nit triggers from the universe counter force.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.76,0:32:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Force requires, triggers counter force.\NTherefore it consumes endless energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.08,0:32:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we see from our annual income tax,\Nit has a voracious appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.08,0:32:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It eats up energy endlessly, endlessly,\Ntrying to overcome obstacles
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.08,0:32:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't understand power.\NPower, which is non-form,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.20,0:32:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,has completely opposite characteristics.\NPower does not consume
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.20,0:32:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,any energy at all.\NPower instead radiates energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.46,0:32:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So power would be like gravity.\NGravity just stands there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.46,0:32:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It just stands there\Nand it influences everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.46,0:32:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time,\Nmore profoundly than any other factor actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.06,0:32:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun just shines,\Nradiates forth energy to the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.06,0:33:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Not selectively, not onto this plant\Nand not on that plant,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.06,0:33:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but onto everything and everyone.\NIt just radiates forth endless energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.15,0:33:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So power then is more profound.\NAnd because it does not consume energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.72,0:33:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it outlasts force.\NWhen you put power and force together,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.72,0:33:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually power wins out\Nbecause it doesn't need any additional supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.79,0:33:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It just stands there until force runs out of ammunition\Nand then falls over of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.94,0:33:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice that the energy fields from 200 up then\Nare the beginning of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.94,0:33:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,200 down on our calibrated level there,\Nyou'll see it has to do with force
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.32,0:33:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has to do with emotionality\Nand it leads to exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.68,0:33:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only so much fear,\Nso much grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.68,0:33:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so many tears,\Nso much pridefulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.68,0:34:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so much aggression\Nwhen you finally run out of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.41,0:34:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Once it's no longer a novelty\Nand once you've gotten squeezed all the drama you can out of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.41,0:34:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it sort of loses its appeal.\NPower on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.89,0:34:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,such as the most common example in human experiences,\Nthe power of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.89,0:34:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,power emanates and radiates endlessly\Nand it originates out of the essence of its own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.27,0:34:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So power then is the radiation of creation expressing itself\Nin ways that influence all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.51,0:34:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,without the expenditure of any energy\Nand without causing any reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.67,0:34:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So power doesn't cause a reaction.\NSo there's no counter,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.67,0:34:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no counter reaction to power\Nand there's always counter reaction to force.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.67,0:35:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got any questions thus far?\NWere there circumstances around 1986,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.76,0:35:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,outward circumstances?\NYes, what happened in 1986,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.16,0:35:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you see you don't know which is cause and which is effect\Nand which is merely concordance,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.42,0:35:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which brings us, we'll talk about\Ncreation versus causation and what that brings to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.46,0:35:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened at that time was\Nan evolution of consciousness that reached a point
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.46,0:35:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that was marked historically by the,\Nwhat was it, the confluence of the something or others,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.41,0:35:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what was it in 1986, the confluence of the?\NHarmonic convergence, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.08,0:35:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Harmonic convergence was the event that marked that time.\NIt didn't cause it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.15,0:35:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was the coalition of all those forces\Nat that moment did express them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.60,0:36:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and themselves and people everywhere\Njoined in prayer for peace
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.92,0:36:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was an enormous power of prayer\Ngoing on at that time as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.68,0:36:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And a concordance of evolution of consciousness\Nthroughout time, it reached a jumping off place
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.68,0:36:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and crossed over that line unnoticed by anyone,\Nunnoticed, nobody noticed it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.71,0:36:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the most significant event in all of human history\Nsadly occurred without a single headline.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.96,0:36:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All of life is different as a result.\NIt is so profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.22,0:36:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the overall temperature of the globe\Ngoing up two degrees, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.22,0:36:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the children on the street don't notice it,\Nbut the difference in production of vegetation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.22,0:36:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the planet, you know,\Nruns into billions of tons of,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.22,0:36:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the profound implication and effect\Non all of life on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.44,0:36:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,by even a couple of degrees shift\Nwhich goes, you know, generally unnoticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.64,0:37:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we had,\Nit wasn't just the size of the jump from 190 to 207,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.64,0:37:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but the fact that it crossed a critical line,\Nthat was what was critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.96,0:37:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difference between 31 degrees and 32 degrees\Nis quite a bit, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.96,0:37:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because at 31 everything turns to solid or ice\Nand at 32 it turns to water,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.99,0:37:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's only one degree,\Nbut what a significant degree that,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.99,0:37:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same thing occurs at 212, you know,\N211 is water,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.40,0:37:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,212 is steam and turns into gas,\Nso that crossing over to 207 was very profound
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.66,0:37:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because now the quality, the quality of change,\Nit wasn't just a quantitative change,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.66,0:37:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a qualitative change.\NSo we can feel somewhat optimistic
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.04,0:37:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that the future then of mankind\Nis obviously quite a bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.04,0:37:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be quite different,\Nor is already quite different
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.04,0:38:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,than it was or could be.\NAt 190 it could not improve,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.23,0:38:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it really couldn't do anything more\Nthan what it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.19,0:38:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,At 207 almost anything,\Nit can go almost anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.19,0:38:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will see all these changes of,\Nshifts of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.19,0:38:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,now that we're aware that this is taking place,\Nyou can see it in the headlines,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.19,0:38:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't see it before,\Nyou thought it was just a sequence of current events,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.51,0:38:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not just a sequence,\Nyou see a shift in the nature, in the tone,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.51,0:38:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and we hear people talking about the quality of life,\Nthe quality of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.57,0:38:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,not only just keeping people alive longer,\Nbut, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.60,0:38:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,ensuring the quality of life,\Nquality of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.99,0:38:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,HMOs are not too interested in the quality of life,\Nbut mankind is, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.28,0:39:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean individuals?\NI'm sure even the frogs felt it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.24,0:39:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but they didn't express it, you see.\NSo a lot of people felt the shift,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.24,0:39:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and they weren't sure what it is,\Nand so I'm just trying to define it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.24,0:39:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and make it rather specific,\Nso that we know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.78,0:39:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to bring up then,\Nthe difference between creation and causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.61,0:39:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a very significant understanding,\Nbecause from 200 down,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.68,0:39:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of form,\Nthe world of force,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.87,0:39:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you're dealing in what is termed causality.\NThe world's understanding of what makes things happen
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.32,0:39:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,within the visible domain\Nis that it's like billiard balls,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.32,0:39:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A hits B hits C,\Nand you have a sequence of causalities,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.32,0:39:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and this explains the phenomena\Nthat are witnessed within the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.44,0:39:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at the world from a different viewpoint,\Nfrom the non-linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.79,0:40:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see that no such a thing happens at all.\NFirst of all, sequence is only a phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.79,0:40:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in human consciousness,\Nit has no objective reality of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.08,0:40:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sequence is a sequence of perception.\NYou see this, then you see that,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.08,0:40:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then you see that,\Njust because you saw them sequentially,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.08,0:40:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that it's happening sequentially.\NThe whole idea that there's a happening out there
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.24,0:40:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is an invention within the mind.\NThe only place a happening occurs
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.24,0:40:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is in your own mind.\NIn the world there isn't such a thing as a happening or an event.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.10,0:40:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can witness anything out there and say,\Nstart now, end now,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.10,0:40:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's an event.\NYou can make the event this long,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.10,0:40:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make the event this long,\Nit's when you say it starts,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.10,0:40:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's when you say it stops.\NSo in the world there is no events.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.61,0:40:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing really that requires\Nan explanation of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.61,0:40:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what you're witnessing\Nis the sequence of revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.61,0:41:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're really saying is creation.\NThe common argument,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.82,0:41:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the creationist versus the evolutionist.\NWhat you're seeing,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.88,0:41:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what's actually being seen\Nis the way creation comes about, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.68,0:41:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Power starts at the top\Nand then it radiates down sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.00,0:41:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,like a series of step-down transitions\Nand transformers has become the used example.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.76,0:41:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,From the unmanifest,\Ninvisible domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.05,0:41:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in which there is no form,\Nthat which is the onus
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.84,0:41:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which all of creation occurs.\NOut of the unmanifest comes the manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.84,0:41:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of the unmanifest is infinite.\NThe power of the unmanifest is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.96,0:41:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Even within the domain of advanced theoretical physics\Nwe know that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.96,0:42:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the amount of potential power\Nin one cubic inch of space
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.56,0:42:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is equivalent to the entire mass of the universe.\NIn any cubic inch of invisible space
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.72,0:42:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,potential energy, the power,\Nis greater than the equivalence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.59,0:42:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the mass of the entire universe.\NThat's one cubic inch.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.36,0:42:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's a quarter of an inch.\NThe understanding of this then is
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.08,0:42:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that the power of the unmanifest,\Nthat which is beyond form,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.08,0:42:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that out of which form arises,\Nis infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.08,0:42:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite.\NUnending.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.24,0:42:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the unmanifest arises the manifest.\NWe observe that in,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.70,0:42:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we observe that in meditation\Nwhere you notice
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.47,0:43:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if you start\Nasking yourself what is it that's witnessing,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.82,0:43:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it that's observing,\Nyou go through the various layers of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.82,0:43:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,until finally you get to awareness\Nof the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.56,0:43:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The interesting thing is\Nyou go higher and higher in your meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.56,0:43:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you'll notice\Nthat the levels are impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.56,0:43:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is witnessing,\Nthe content of your thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.91,0:43:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,or your feelingness,\Nis self-existent.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.29,0:43:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not a personal you at all.\NAnd you find that out of habit
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.39,0:43:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you've called it me,\Nbut when you examine it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.48,0:43:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize it's not really a me\Nany more than protoplasm is a me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.48,0:43:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you'd say,\Ntheoretically this is me,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.48,0:43:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and if I pinch it, it feels like me,\Nbut actually it's not me
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.48,0:43:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because if I take it off and throw it away\NI haven't lost any me at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.48,0:43:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still the same me, so.\NThen,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.35,0:43:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the argument between\Nevolution
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.62,0:43:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and creation is a fallacy.\NActually, they're one and the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.62,0:44:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,\Nbecause evolution is nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.32,0:44:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,except the way in which\Ncreation manifests itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.42,0:44:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if there is creation at all,\Nthen
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.03,0:44:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a continuous ongoing event,\Na continuous ongoing event.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.03,0:44:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand the nature of God\Nis to realize that no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.60,0:44:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is an arbitrary moment somewhere in history.\NDid God suddenly roll the dice
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.60,0:44:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and then go off to retire, see?\NWhich is the common viewpoint, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.62,0:44:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that which is infinite\Nand that which is forever
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.62,0:44:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is beyond form\Nis its nature to continuously manifest creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.42,0:44:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and as we see the unfolding of creation\Nwe think that's time
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.42,0:44:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and we think that's evolution.\NEvolution then occurs on the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.87,0:44:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see the little animals and\Nplants and people manifesting
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.87,0:44:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in what we call time\Nbecause that's the way
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.90,0:45:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the universe is created.\NSo, creation is continuous and ongoing,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.90,0:45:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,never ending.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.65,0:45:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The person says,\Nhow can I know the existence of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.00,0:45:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\NGod is that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.12,0:45:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which existence arises.\NSo, the very fact that anything or everyone has existence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.15,0:45:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is the creation of God,\Ncreation of God
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.15,0:45:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is existence itself.\NSo, we don't find
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.92,0:45:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness in the future,\Nwe don't find it clinging to the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.92,0:45:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We find it by focusing on this instant.\NThe joy of this instant
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.65,0:45:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is the realization,\Nthe recognition,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.65,0:45:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness\Nthe feelingness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.65,0:45:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is the presence of God\Nthat is sustaining my existence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.81,0:45:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,this very moment\Nand the existence of everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.81,0:46:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that I am\Nis proof of the existence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.72,0:46:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's all you need.\NWhen I studied theology,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.49,0:46:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an atheist at the time,\Nbut I got a straight A in theology
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.56,0:46:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nanyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.61,0:46:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the arguments for God's existence\Nreally blew my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.61,0:46:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,\Nthat wouldn't make an atheist out of anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.61,0:46:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on first cause, please.\NSo, what they're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.80,0:46:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is how the mind thinks.\NThey're not talking about God at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.80,0:46:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To the mind, that would seem\Nthat all causes must have a first cause
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.80,0:46:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and the prime cause would then be God.\NBut you see how that's really just
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.80,0:46:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,poking around in the intellect.\NYou're circling around in the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.80,0:46:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you calibrate the energy fuel of that,\NI would say it's in the low 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.09,0:46:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In the low 400s, people are so\Nenamored of the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.09,0:47:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can think now,\Nthat they try to think,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.09,0:47:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,use thinkingness and logic\Nto answer everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.09,0:47:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We have politically correct answers to everything.\NThis comes out of the low 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.09,0:47:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, you know,\Nwe think of a corresponding formula,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.09,0:47:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,get everybody behind it,\Nit'll solve problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.09,0:47:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll pass a law against it.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.09,0:47:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to stop something\Nis to pass a law against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.09,0:47:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day in the paper,\Nthere should be a law against something.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.09,0:47:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Pass a law against it.\NNow you've cured it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.09,0:47:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's wonderful.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.09,0:47:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway,\Nthe low 400s are enamored
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.09,0:47:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinkingness and the intellect\Nand get carried away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.22,0:47:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And they write most of our laws,\Nand they write legislation,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.38,0:47:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these things that sound so erudite.\NExcept they have a hidden downside,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.99,0:47:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and then once you put them into operation,\Nyou find the downside is worse than the upside was.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.99,0:47:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll give welfare to all the mothers,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.05,0:47:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but the thing is that they put in there,\Nso long as there's not a man in the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.05,0:48:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,well,\Nwhat happened as soon as they had welfare?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.24,0:48:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's no man in the house,\Nall the men left.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.24,0:48:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the inner city,\Nthere wasn't no fathers anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.24,0:48:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should they be?\NIf she yee-yanks around,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.24,0:48:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no money.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.24,0:48:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the unseen downside comes around\Nto kick out the good of the upside.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.24,0:48:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And so,\Nthe intellect is limited
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.24,0:48:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in what it can accomplish in society.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.44,0:48:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we talked about creation\Nand its contrast with evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.44,0:48:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Ncreation,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.44,0:48:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nit's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.68,0:48:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very complex thing.\NIt's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.80,0:48:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very complex thing.\NIt's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.80,0:48:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very complex thing.\NIt's a very complex thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.22,0:48:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Ncreation comes out of the essence of,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.44,0:48:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,\Neverything is what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.66,0:48:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,as a perfect expression of its own essence.\NNothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.66,0:48:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no need for anything to cause anything else.\NEverything in the universe gives forth a radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.72,0:48:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a vibration,\Nan energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.72,0:48:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that is characteristic,\Nindividual,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.36,0:48:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and unique.\NEverything in the universe sets forth an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.46,0:49:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and a vibration.\NThroughout all of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.49,0:49:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is a vibration.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.97,0:49:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated levels of consciousness\Nare really the levels
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.97,0:49:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,at which these vibrational fields\Ntend to congregate.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.97,0:49:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They tend to congregate.\NAnd,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.29,0:49:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,using chaos theory,\Nnon-linear dynamics,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.29,0:49:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,says that within what appears to be chaotic,\Nthere is really a hidden inner attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.74,0:49:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Within what appears to be a chaotic flight of birds,\Nfor instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.74,0:49:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there is\Nan energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.00,0:49:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can actually map out that energy field\Nand draw it as a design,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.00,0:49:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that the birds,\Nwhen you see them moving around,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.25,0:49:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you see these huge flocks that all feel in unison like this,\Nor you see them fish underwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.25,0:49:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions of fish all turn in unison.\NWithin the left brain of logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.89,0:50:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a presumption that all these fish are somehow looking at each other\Nand keeping two and a half inches from each other
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.89,0:50:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and staying in line like a bunch of\Nairplanes out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.89,0:50:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,\Nwhere the guys are looking at their instruments,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.89,0:50:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nhey,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.89,0:50:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Joe,\Nyou're getting a quarter of an inch too close to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.89,0:50:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hear all these little fish\Nand little birds and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.72,0:50:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,\Nthe minute you look at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.72,0:50:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize there's some kind of hidden,\Nyou can actually see,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.72,0:50:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the hidden energy field\Nin like an invisible attractor field,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.72,0:50:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's shaped like this,\Nand each one,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.72,0:50:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,each one singly is following that pattern\Nwithin their own mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.72,0:50:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of them\Nis singly following,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.72,0:50:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,within their mind,\Nthat pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.72,0:50:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't even know what the other one's over there doing,\Nsurprisingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.72,0:50:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one is being led by this organization\Nof this intrinsic energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.20,0:50:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which in itself is extremely beautiful.\NI mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.20,0:50:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see the field itself.\NYou're going to design it and project it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.20,0:50:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and in graphics,\Nyou would see the beauty of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.27,0:51:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And not only are dynamics and chaos there,\Nthese are called attractors,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.68,0:51:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,hidden attractor fields.\NIt was first discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.12,0:51:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,by Lorenz who discovered it\Nwhen he advanced computers,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.25,0:51:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,allowed Lorenz to examine\Nthe history of weather
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.26,0:51:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,over a great expanse of time.\NAnd weather had never been predictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.26,0:51:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not within the predictable.\NYou cannot use a computer
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.74,0:51:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell us what the weather's going to be next week.\NBut he found that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.38,0:51:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,by organizing all this data\Nover the centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.60,0:51:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was within it\Na pattern that revealed
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.66,0:51:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was an organizational\Nhub, you might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.82,0:51:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,emanating forth as the changing\Nweather from century to century.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.62,0:52:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And he got a computer graphic of it,\Nand it's called Lorenz's Butterfly,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.62,0:52:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,very, very famous,\NLorenz's Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.91,0:52:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And it looks something like a butterfly.\NAnd that was the organizational field behind
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.91,0:52:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,weather over the centuries.\NAnd you can see the same pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.32,0:52:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see on TV\Nthese beautiful migrations
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.39,0:52:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of birds wheeling about\Nor the fish under the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.61,0:52:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you see an energy pattern\Nhidden from sight,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.61,0:52:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,revealed by their movement,\Nbut it doesn't exist in a measurable domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.80,0:52:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't go out there\Nand with a yardstick
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.80,0:52:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,find this invisible pattern\Nand measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.80,0:52:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So it decides it didn't really exist,\Nthat there was no organizational pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.02,0:52:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,These calibrated levels of consciousness\Nthen are really,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.27,0:52:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what we've tuned in on is that\Nwith the energy field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.97,0:52:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to which man is subject\Nand participates,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.97,0:53:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there is hidden energy fields\Nwhich tend to dominate that field.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.97,0:53:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Our consciousness tends to be dominated by,\Nit becomes influenced,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.31,0:53:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely influenced\Nby the energy fields to which we subscribe.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.00,0:53:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you subscribe\Nto a certain energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.00,0:53:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you're really asking\Nthat energy field to come in
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.13,0:53:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and dominate your consciousness.\NAnd you now
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.03,0:53:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,will feel a certain allegiance\Nto these types of attitudes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.03,0:53:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can calibrate\Nthese various energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.47,0:53:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and identify them as typical\Nsocial attitudes,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.69,0:53:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,vocational proclivities,\Neven crime rates,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.69,0:53:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihood of various health phenomena.\NBecause they're characteristic
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.82,0:54:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of certain energy fields\Nand certainly energy levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.48,0:54:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The most critical one to know about\Nis over or under 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.48,0:54:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to show you kinesiology\Nand I'm sure everybody here is familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.48,0:54:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here has experienced it?\NEverybody here experienced kinesiology?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.48,0:54:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How many have not?\NHow many have not?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.64,0:54:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's put it that way.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.64,0:54:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We will do a very brief exercise\Nin which we demonstrate the basics of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.64,0:54:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But,\Nwhat these energy fields then tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.64,0:54:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is what can be expected.\NMore significantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.64,0:54:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it tells us what is that level of truth.\NSo mankind has a great dilemma
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.86,0:54:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of history.\NHe doesn't know the difference between truth
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.86,0:54:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and he doesn't know the difference\Nbetween truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.86,0:54:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And he has no means of discerning it.\NThe entire legal system
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.86,0:54:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is set upon man's ignorance, is it not?\NWhy do you need 12 people
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.86,0:54:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to decide what the truth is?\NAnd you can't decide truth
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.89,0:54:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,by voting for it.\NYes, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.89,0:55:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't.\NI mean, what a ridiculous system, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.89,0:55:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.\NSo mankind has had a terrible time
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.63,0:55:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,killing each other\Nand excommunicating people
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.63,0:55:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for old Galileo.\NIt took the Church almost 500 years
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.63,0:55:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to say,\Nokay, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.72,0:55:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very pleased\Nwhen Galileo got off the hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.72,0:55:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really,\Nfor a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.72,0:55:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I really had a problem\Nwith the Church, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.72,0:55:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought,\Ngeez, it took you 500 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.72,0:55:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I mean,\Nwhat's 450 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.72,0:55:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it get off the track,\Nyou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.72,0:55:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, poor old Galileo\Nfinally got off the hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.72,0:55:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, I felt better.\NI was scared to write about
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.72,0:55:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the things\NI wrote about God.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.72,0:55:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what happened to Galileo.\NHe was only talking about planets, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.72,0:55:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, here you're talking about\Ntruth throughout all of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.72,0:55:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you could be right.\NSo, I'm glad the Church
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.72,0:56:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,has given up frying people\Nso now I can publish the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.04,0:56:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it is a sharp razor.\NIt's a razor's edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.04,0:56:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth or falsehood,\Nfirst time in mankind's history,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.04,0:56:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind has had to face this.\NFirst time man has ever had to face
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.84,0:56:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that man cannot tell truth from falsehood.\NThat is so frightening
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.84,0:56:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that very few people\Nhave really picked up
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.84,0:56:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the significance of this book at all.\NA group of leaders did
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.84,0:56:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and they invited me to a certain country\Nwhere she and I played quite a role
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.84,0:56:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in shifting the whole paradigm.\NBut mostly people don't get
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.03,0:56:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what it's about.\NBut you can tell the truth or falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.03,0:56:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of anything within an instant.\NThe interesting thing is that
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.06,0:56:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell the level of truth.\NWell, I had at home the,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.06,0:56:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,collected the great books\Nof the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.06,0:56:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a wonderful find.\NI came across them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.96,0:56:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It used to cost me 500 bucks.\NIt's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.56,0:56:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.\NIt's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.56,0:56:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.\NIt's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.56,0:56:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.\NIt's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.60,0:56:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great book.\NIt's a great book.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.98,0:56:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And published in 1933,\NUniversity of Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.98,0:57:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, goes through Descartes and Kant\Nand all the great thinkers
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.04,0:57:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.\NAnd it's a wonderful collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.04,0:57:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest thinkers of the\NWestern world throughout all of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.72,0:57:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The last one in the series,\NI think, is Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.72,0:57:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway, all of this erudition\Nand it is fascinating and,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.09,0:57:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, when I was a kid\NI was into reading Plato
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.31,0:57:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and stuff while other kids\Nwould go to school
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.53,0:57:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but all the great thinkers\Nthroughout the time
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.53,0:57:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and things, think of all of them. Anyway, being a misfit, I\Nbe sitting home reading Plato and Socrates and stuff. Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.94,0:57:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,all this dissertation throughout the centuries has all been about\None single thing. How do you tell the truth from falsehood? That's all it's about.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.28,0:57:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All this collection of the greatest thinking of all the great thinkers of mankind\Nare all dealing, nor have they even solved, how do you tell
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.19,0:58:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth from falsehood? Well, to us it's a snap, of course.\NBecause we have this wondrous chart here in front of us
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.32,0:58:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,which they did not have. And what this chart really says\Nis truth is what you think it is within certain parameters.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.47,0:58:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is not that truth is relative, it's that truth is\Nperceptualized completely differently depending on a level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.31,0:58:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What is truth? That one level of consciousness is ridiculous\Nat another. If a person's consciousness is at a
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.36,0:58:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,very rudimentary level,\Nwe have to teach them that killing people is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.23,0:58:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do it, we will electrocute you.\NThat didn't make sense, did it? Well, if you do, we will put you in prison forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.60,0:59:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to be free, we'll kill you until you want to be free, right?\NBigger, better bombs. Anyway, truth is relative and it depends on context.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.60,0:59:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's never been said before.\NThere's no such thing as truth without delineation of context.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.74,0:59:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that passes as truth is fallacious if it's missing the context.\NAnd there you have the endless spin put on truth throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.84,0:59:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't define context, anybody can say anything and reframe it in some context as truth.\NAnd prove it as truth within that context.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.25,0:59:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So unless you delineate context then,\Nuh,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.40,0:59:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,any claim to truth is, uh, fallacious.\NSo here we have the various levels of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.66,0:59:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say, um, let's just do a few things, uh, for fun.\NSo, we'll do a few things for fun. Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.46,1:00:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We said, first of all, the critical line is 200. 200.\NThat which is above 200 is concordant with love.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.46,1:00:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is below 200 is not concordant with love.\NIn fact, people below 200 are repulsed by love.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.46,1:00:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All the politically correct do-gooders out there.\NOh, we should just love them and they'll get better.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.68,1:00:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that people below 200 are repulsed by love.\NIt's nauseating.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.00,1:00:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Please leave us alone.\NDisgust.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.48,1:00:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys, the people under 200 are disgusted by loving, understanding, wonderful, compassionate approaches?\NThey think it's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.24,1:00:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They've told me so.\NI'm chief of staff at a presidential residence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.54,1:00:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Treatment center with 54 teenage girls.\NMany of whom are really quite committed to negativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.94,1:01:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a wonderful, kind, clean, it's a marvelous place.\NIt's a dream come true.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.97,1:01:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say to a kid who just came in from Black Canyon jail.\NSo, how do you like it here?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.04,1:01:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She goes,\NThank you. I guess the food wasn't so good.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.68,1:01:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the attitude is, you know,\NSo, you see, that which is negative views love as an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.60,1:01:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh-ho.\NAnything under 200, then, views love as the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.02,1:01:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy.\NDon't you understand? You're the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.02,1:01:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a person ask about it.\NWell, we just said it's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.75,1:01:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We check ourself all the time.\NA lot of times something comes out original and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.75,1:01:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, that's wild something.\NHow so? Okay, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.19,1:01:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything,\Neverything that we study,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.19,1:02:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that we believe in,\Nevery teacher that we follow should be calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.19,1:02:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know the level of truth in which the person is speaking.\NFirst of all, to make sure that they're legitimate, over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.19,1:02:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And to give you an idea of what level of reality,\Nfrom what level of reality are they speaking,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.02,1:02:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you know what it is you're listening to.\NSo much of spiritual confusion in the spiritual community
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.15,1:02:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to mixing levels.\NNew mixing levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.15,1:02:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,New mixing levels.\NSome gurus said this, and they quoted out of context.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.34,1:02:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it's out of context,\Nand you don't know who is,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.34,1:02:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,why it was said to whom, and for what reason,\Nand in what context of truth you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.23,1:02:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we advise everybody to do\Nis to check out the level of truth of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.64,1:02:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the writer, the speaker, the course.\NDon't accept anything on faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.56,1:02:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NWhy should you not accept anything on faith?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.56,1:03:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if mankind was onto the truth,\Nall these centuries,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.56,1:03:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,our life would be totally different, wouldn't it?\NThere wouldn't have been any World War II or World War I.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.56,1:03:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't be any plague.\NThere wouldn't be AIDS all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.63,1:03:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't have been taxes rising.\NAll this negativity prevails
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.95,1:03:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because nobody checked out the level of truth of the speaker.\NIf you checked out Adolf Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.17,1:03:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it wouldn't have lasted too long.\NShall we give up our entire life and serve this furor?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.17,1:03:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You make sure I don't go weak, for God's sake.\NRip you off.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.17,1:03:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He ripped off the whole country, didn't he?\NHe ripped off the whole economy,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.30,1:03:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole generation.\NWiped out all the young people.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.30,1:03:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Corrupted all their morals.\NDestroyed their country.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.40,1:03:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroyed everything but beauty.\NBrought about the destruction of the Cathedrals of Cologne.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.88,1:03:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's see.\NPicture something or someone you love.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.11,1:04:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Not picture something you don't love.\NSo that's the basic demonstration.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.15,1:04:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,People say they've studied this over and over.\NThey can't get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.15,1:04:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only about 18 seconds to get how to look at ideology.\NI watched Dr. Diamond do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.15,1:04:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, true.\NFalse.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.15,1:04:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What more is there to know?\NYou don't have to really know anything more.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.24,1:04:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple.\NThe basic mechanism, however, is not all that simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.08,1:04:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Diamond didn't get it,\Nand neither did anybody,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.36,1:04:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,until we saw that what we're touching into\Nis not local causality, but non-local.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.62,1:04:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is non-local.\NWhat we're tapping into
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.00,1:04:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is the capacity of non-local consciousness\Nto recognize truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.00,1:04:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to recognize love from non-love.\NThe Course in Miracles, I think, as I said in the book,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.85,1:04:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is most of the people here in the Course in Miracles?\NEverybody?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.85,1:04:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wonderful.\NAlright, so,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.88,1:05:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Course in Miracles itself calibrates at 600.\NLet's see if it still does.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.94,1:05:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Course in Miracles, we have permission to ask, resist.\NCalibrates at 600, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.10,1:05:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 610, resist.\NCalibrates precisely at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.74,1:05:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Very interesting.\NVery significant.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.54,1:05:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,See, to know the Course in Miracles calibrates at 600\Ngives you a whole different orientation
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.67,1:05:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of what the Course in Miracles is,\Nwhat it's for,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.67,1:05:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,where it fits into the overall level of truth\Nas it's been expressed throughout the history of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.83,1:05:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,600, curiously, is the same level,\Nsame as the level of truth in kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.98,1:05:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology, if you ask,\Nwhat is the level of reliability of truth in kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.30,1:05:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it says 600.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.30,1:05:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Course in Miracles is at 600.\NBefore I did it with Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.52,1:05:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in Lewis, enlightenment begins at 600.\NAnd 600, then, is the transition
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.52,1:05:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,from form to non-form,\Nfrom the linear to the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.52,1:06:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Once a person reaches 600,\Nin our society, we say they're enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.60,1:06:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The chance is one in less than 10 million,\Nbut it does occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.60,1:06:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When it does, it's usually recorded in history\Nbecause it's unusual.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.72,1:06:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,However, a lot of people, when they hit 600,\Njust blitz out and leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.62,1:06:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody rears them.\NNobody rears them.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.70,1:06:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole world wants you to resume this body\Nand continue on with this pageant here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.20,1:06:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it doesn't seem very attractive to do, you see.\NBut if you still have something,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.48,1:06:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're not at 1,000, you're only at 600,\Nyou're still vulnerable to love.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.64,1:06:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of love,\Nyou may decide to come back into the body and resume.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.00,1:06:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that's attractive.\NYou've got to let go of it and get over it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.92,1:06:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to calibrate\Nthe level of truth of everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.21,1:07:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book Power Versus Force,\Nwe calibrated every chapter.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.21,1:07:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated the book as a whole, every chapter.\NWe went over every page, every paragraph, every sentence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.34,1:07:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Examined the entire book using kinesiology.\NIs everything on this page correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.60,1:07:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everything on this page correct?\NWe found we didn't find one error.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.63,1:07:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We did find one error.\NAnd we said, is there anything out in this chapter?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.63,1:07:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They said yes.\NAnd then we went page by page.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.92,1:07:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something on this page?\NNo, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.92,1:07:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We got the page was on.\NIs it in the top half of the page?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.92,1:07:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Bottom of the top half of the page.\NIs it this paragraph?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.92,1:07:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSecond sentence?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.92,1:07:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,First sentence?\NOh, I got the word.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.92,1:07:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It was John Lennon.\NWe took John Lennon out of the sentence,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.92,1:07:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it was perfect.\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.23,1:07:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the truth are we talking about now?\NAll right, so right now we're talking at 750.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.70,1:07:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, we calibrate what we are saying\Nfrom moment to moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.80,1:08:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind of material, the consciousness\Nfrom which this speech is being expressed, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.98,1:08:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,coming at this moment from about 750.\NSo if we go back to our levels of consciousness then,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.01,1:08:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I think when I did this we didn't know much\Nabout 700 to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.24,1:08:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we didn't.\NWe stopped at 600 because we didn't have a chance
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.16,1:08:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to check out what goes on from 600 on up.\NThe levels from 700 to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.54,1:08:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we've been working on more recently.\NAnd the eye of the eye has to do primarily with those levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.83,1:08:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,700 to 1,000.\NWhat are those fields of consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.08,1:08:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they represent?\NWhat is the understanding that arises in them?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.76,1:08:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The 700s are the levels of Ramana Maharshi,\NNisargadatta Maharaj,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.98,1:08:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,great and famous saints throughout history.\NAnd then Hoang Po.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.62,1:09:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoang Po, the 6th Patriarch.\NHe said 700 resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.88,1:09:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 700 resists.\N780 resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.88,1:09:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 800 resists.\NHe said 790 resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.55,1:09:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,After that Hoang Po, the transmission of mind.\NIt is 790.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.60,1:09:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There are not many people in the upper one\Nso we didn't spend much time investigating it
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.60,1:09:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,until recent times.\NThe most interesting thing we found about those levels
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.83,1:09:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the level of the avatar is 1,000.\NThe human nervous system cannot tolerate
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.96,1:09:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy that calibrates over 1,000.\Nthe calibration of Buddha, Krishna, Jesus Christ, all came out at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.56,1:09:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Their missions were somewhat different, and that's something we sort of asked recently.\NThe lady who read our work and called up Susan and said she was concerned about the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.17,1:10:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that she felt somewhat guilty as a Catholic, adhering to a lot of Buddhist principles, you know.\NCatholicism tends to sort of have a certain rigidity about its own dogma.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.93,1:10:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So she had felt a certain conflict between Buddhism and Catholicism.\NAnd she and Susie talked about it over the phone, and we thought about it and reflected on it
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.04,1:10:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and checked that ourselves.\NBut it was just a difference of missions.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.17,1:10:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, they both calibrated at a thousand.\NSo if Buddha's a thousand and Christ is a thousand, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.25,1:10:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the relationship between their teachings?\NAnd what we got was that the purpose of the Buddha was to teach enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.39,1:10:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha doesn't talk about salvation and the Christian sense of salvation.\NThe Buddha really presses towards enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.12,1:10:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus doesn't talk about enlightenment.\NHe talks about salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.20,1:10:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That used to bother me, too.\NI thought, how come Jesus Christ never mentions anything about enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.43,1:11:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,when he's at a thousand the same as the Buddha?\NYou know, the Buddha didn't talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.40,1:11:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The aim of Buddhism is not to reach a sufficient level that a savior comes and saves you\Nand takes you to heaven, see.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.86,1:11:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Except there is pure land Buddhism.\NPure land Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.92,1:11:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure land Buddhism.\NPure land Buddhism is sort of practical, like Jesus Christ is practical.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.16,1:11:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds to me like Jesus Christ said,\Nthe likelihood of people becoming enlightened in this lifetime is very, very slim.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.50,1:11:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of teaching people how to become enlightened,\Nwhich is not going to be too attractive to them and not appeal to many
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.26,1:11:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and probably not going to happen in one in a hundred million,\Nlet's get practical and talk about what is achievable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.75,1:11:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Christian principles are achievable.\NAnd they don't take you into the five hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.11,1:11:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And from there, you obviously go to heaven.\NAnd from heaven, you can then go the rest of the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.60,1:11:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the thinking was, and it still is in many sides of Buddhism,\Nthat the negativity of this planet is so intense
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.23,1:12:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that the likelihood of achieving enlightenment is, you know, so slim\Nthat it's not really a practical way to go for many people.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.98,1:12:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And so new land Buddhism really says practice spiritual principles\Nand you will then, the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.93,1:12:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha of salvation, Amitabha Buddha will then become your savior\Nand represent you in heaven and from the new land,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.59,1:12:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which is really one of the levels of heaven,\Nyou can then from there shoot for enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.26,1:12:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus Christ then sounded to me like a practical person.\NHe's talking to, you know, the people of his time were very uneducated, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.22,1:12:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what he was, you know, what he,\Nrecommended was to avoid sin and follow virtue.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.80,1:13:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do that, then you will qualify for salvation,\Nwhich means starting to go to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.96,1:13:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's bring it up to date in modern terminology then.\NModern terminology, we'd say,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.33,1:13:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what Jesus Christ said was avoid everything\Nthat calibrates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.29,1:13:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Simple enough, that's really all he said.\NDon't hang out below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.36,1:13:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are what he calls sin.\NThe reason is,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.32,1:13:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the consequences of sin are very unpleasant.\NAnd Jesus did not recommend that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.36,1:13:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hang out below 200,\Nyou will not be pleased with the end result, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.25,1:13:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So he was very practical.\NHe said, in his own inner self,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.36,1:13:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he said, enlightenment is for so few.\NWhy not think of the many?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.59,1:13:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Much like Mahayana Buddhism is concerned with the many,\Nand Hinayana is with the few.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.32,1:13:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ was very practical and realized\Nthat only so much was possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.36,1:14:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we found out something very interesting.\NLet's recapitulate what we found out.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.71,1:14:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,People who calibrate under 200 are able to get to heaven.\NThat's true or false?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.02,1:14:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They're able to get to heaven.\NUnder 200, they're not able to get to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.70,1:14:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Under 200, you have subscribed and committed\Nto that which is false, negative, destructive, evil,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.04,1:14:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever you want to call it.\NUnder 200, unaided, one cannot get into heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.49,1:14:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing.\NTherefore, why did Christ die?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.10,1:14:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He, and this suddenly came to us as an intuition, he said,\Nhe died to save all the people under 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.93,1:15:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ died to save the souls,\Nor to give the souls of those under 200 to exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.08,1:15:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus Christ, who died for all of mankind,\Ndied because his energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.15,1:15:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,his energy field was so powerful\Nthat it counterbalanced the entire negativity
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.15,1:15:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of everything and everyone under 200,\Nwithout whom they would end up in hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.20,1:15:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very interesting.\NTo accept Jesus Christ as one's savior, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.00,1:15:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is crucial if your energy field is under 200.\NOver 200, you don't have to be saved by Jesus
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.35,1:15:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to heaven.\NLet's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.82,1:15:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to over 200.\NYou've got enough spiritual truth within you already
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.41,1:15:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that you'll inevitably, eventually go the whole route.\NUnder 200, you're like a drowning person.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.31,1:16:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot save yourself.\NSo Jesus Christ as savior, then, is a reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.62,1:16:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,which we can calibrate the truth of this very day.\NHe died to save the souls of all those people under 200
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.45,1:16:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are so lacking in spiritual truth.\NThere's no way they can navigate towards the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.45,1:16:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To be able to be attracted by the light,\Nyou would have to be attracted by the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.16,1:16:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And we just said before,\Nthat people under 200 are not attracted by the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.12,1:16:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They are repelled by the light.\NRepelled by the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.60,1:16:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So how would those people get this elevation\Nif they're repelled by spiritual truth and light?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.03,1:16:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, I'm happy now.\NJesus Christ makes much more sense to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.03,1:16:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with him totally.\NI think it was a very practical view that he took.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.41,1:16:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And many branches of Buddhism take the same.\NAnd we've got Hindu, Krishna,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.83,1:17:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the ancient Vedas also say\Nthat this time the negativity on the planet is so extreme,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.44,1:17:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of becoming enlightened,\Nit's not too good every 58,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.44,1:17:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One revolution of the Zodiac, or whatever it is,\None aeon is in the universe for 58,000 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.14,1:17:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,those are the only things.\NAll right, so,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.77,1:17:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the thing about studying the nature of consciousness\Nis you begin to have a context from which
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.77,1:17:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand spiritual teachings,\Na way to fit them together.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.77,1:17:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That which was once mysterious, challenging and undecipherable\Nnow becomes quite logical and comprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.77,1:17:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we want to do by understanding the nature of consciousness\Nis to make comprehensible the incomprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.84,1:17:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that certain information that could not be integrated before\Ncan now be integrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.86,1:18:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of information, once you hear it integrated,\Nthe information itself has enormous power.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.86,1:18:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've heard that, you're going to be a different person.\NThe information itself propels your consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.86,1:18:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason the levels of consciousness of people who read Power vs. Force\Nor hear a lecture like this jump afterwards
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.98,1:18:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is certain information has automatically opened new avenues in their consciousness.\NYou can see those little synapses just being happy,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.98,1:18:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,bzz, bzz, bzz, bzz, all speaking to each other and saying,\Noh, we have to learn from you, we're many a lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.98,1:18:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, how nice, oh, how nice,\Noh, I see, God loves me,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.98,1:18:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, oh, oh, oh.\NThat's the truth, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.98,1:18:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise I wouldn't have existence.\NIf God had you, you wouldn't have existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.98,1:18:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be squished like a bug.\NJust the fact that we're here means that we're okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.20,1:18:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.\NI thought you liked to hear that this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.43,1:18:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you were worried about it.\NWe're all okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.97,1:19:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now that we know we're all okay,\NI think we should take a break, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.76,1:19:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Exhausted ourselves with all this very interesting stuff.\NWe'll take a shirt break.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.76,1:19:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the bust of Newark, isn't it?\NThis is the bust of Newark, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.00,1:19:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I thought we'll resume as long as we're here.\NAs long as we're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.16,1:19:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of things I wanted to talk about today.\NI want to explain karma because there's no,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.16,1:19:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,see, a lot of what I do, really my thrust in the world is,\Nto try and make comprehensible that which has not been made comprehensible throughout time,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.16,1:19:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,due to mistranslations, wrong words,\Nmistranslations from Sanskrit,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.16,1:20:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,through Greek, through Aramaic,\Nmisunderstandings because teachings are heard by people who can tell they're not enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.16,1:20:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore they use the wrong word,\Nthey give the wrong inference.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.16,1:20:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between detached and non-detached,\Nis profound.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.16,1:20:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see most Buddhist literature talks about detached,\Nand detached is different than non-detached,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.16,1:20:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,two different things.\NOr the Buddha has said that there's only one sin,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.09,1:20:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is ignorance.\NNo, that's a mistranslation.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.44,1:20:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to correct some of the mistranslations,\Nmisunderstandings, integrate the understanding of karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.44,1:20:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which is one of the crossovers from Buddhism to Christianity\Nthat many people find difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.02,1:20:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll talk about some of personal thoughts,\Nexperiences,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.52,1:20:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that led to some of these understandings,\Nwho this person is.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.48,1:20:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it says on the syllabus here.\NFamiliarize and explain.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.00,1:21:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Background and qualifications of the speaker and his research,\Nwell that's neat.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.64,1:21:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we'd do that a little bit.\NBecause it'll lead us into some understandings.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.15,1:21:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is speaking is consciousness,\Nyou understand that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.15,1:21:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in the linear domain,\Nyou presume that this physicality here is the person,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.34,1:21:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody presumes there's a Dr. Hawkins here\Nwho's speaking and all this, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.16,1:21:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only consciousness that's speaking, you see.\NIt's only consciousness that's speaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.42,1:21:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm as surprised by what goes on as anyone.\NBecause I'm misled by I,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.42,1:21:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you from where I speak from,\Ndoesn't know what's going to happen either,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.42,1:21:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or what we're even going to talk about today,\Nuntil it happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.42,1:21:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you live in the instant,\Nyou don't have any,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.25,1:21:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing's telling you what's coming up in the future,\Nor what just happened in the past,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.25,1:21:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because neither exists.\NSo, it's always a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.99,1:22:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like riding the crest of a wig.\NWhich is the way to get into the instant present,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.84,1:22:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is to constantly release and let go of everything as it arises,\Nlike a note of music.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.84,1:22:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As the note arises,\Nit's already falling out of its existence, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.91,1:22:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't stay with the music that just once was,\Nnor can you live with the music that hasn't arisen yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.91,1:22:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only ride the note that's rising at the moment.\NAnd that is a method of meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.87,1:22:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can do throughout the day,\Nbut which sort of takes me out of the world considerably.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.70,1:22:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of my problems this morning is I'm not really in the world too well,\Nbut, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.50,1:22:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought to give some organization,\NI would just talk about my own personal experiences,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.50,1:22:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because it says here,\Nbackground of the speaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.50,1:22:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nthinking of the background of the speaker,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.93,1:22:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd have to go back some eons.\NBut before that,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.06,1:23:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime,\Nthe first conscious awareness was
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.06,1:23:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,age three.\NBefore three,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.54,1:23:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,there was nothing but void.\NThree in the word,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.18,1:23:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,three was chronological in terms of the world,\Nthe age of the body was three.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.18,1:23:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, at age three,\Nwhat the world says at age three,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.31,1:23:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,out of void, out of nothingness at all,\Nout of nonexistence,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.27,1:23:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,there was suddenly a profound and stunning\Nawareness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.27,1:23:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just suddenly,\Nsuddenly conscious of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.52,1:23:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence as existence,\Nnot as existence as the physicality,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.52,1:23:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,although the physicality seemed to awake\Nthe awareness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.52,1:23:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was the awareness of existence as existence.\NIt was very intense,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.96,1:23:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was also nonverbal.\NThere was no,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.96,1:23:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,three year old doesn't know such words.\NOh, what a three year old notice they have on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.70,1:24:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nthis consciousness was stunned by
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.70,1:24:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the sudden awareness of existence.\NAnd as soon as there was the awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.70,1:24:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that I exist,\Neven though I wasn't there yet,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.76,1:24:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no existence as existence,\Ninstantly its alternative came up,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.75,1:24:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,its opposite came up,\Nof nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.75,1:24:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And instantly I was frightened.\NInstantly there was the fear of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.23,1:24:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, out of existence arose instantly\Nthe duality of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.23,1:24:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the profound spiritual conundrum,\Nkoan of this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.87,1:24:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Koan.\NHow do you pronounce it?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.47,1:24:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,C-O-H-E-N.\NNo, C-O-K-A-O-A.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.47,1:24:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,K-O-A-N.\NThat was the riddle of this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.28,1:24:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nsomebody will have to make some notes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.50,1:25:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a couple of things we have to talk about.\NWe have to talk about positionality,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.50,1:25:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who's going to be the secretary?\NSomebody make a note.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.76,1:25:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Positionality,\Nwe don't want to forget that,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.76,1:25:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and karma.\NAlright, because
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.17,1:25:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what this represented also was\Nprobably, you know, karmically,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.17,1:25:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where I left off.\NWhere I left off as a Buddhist monk,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.17,1:25:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a Hinayana monk.\NIn some lifetimes,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.17,1:25:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I would always end up as,\Nthe ultimate reality is void.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.17,1:25:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Go out of body and experience void.\NBecause after all,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.17,1:25:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if you think reality is void\Nand you leave the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.17,1:25:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you into?\NYou're into void.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.17,1:25:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,From that lifetime to the next,\Nand then suddenly you're in a new body,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.17,1:25:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with no connecting in the astral realms.\NBecause as a Hinayana Buddhist,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.59,1:25:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't believe in all that stuff.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.59,1:25:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway,\NI think that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.78,1:25:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that happened.\NThat is what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.78,1:25:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My guess is right.\NThat is what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.78,1:25:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo, anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.78,1:25:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,out of voidness,\Nwhich this,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.78,1:25:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,apparently,\NHinayana Buddhist monk felt
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.78,1:26:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was the ultimate reality,\Nsuddenly there was this
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.78,1:26:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.78,1:26:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the first problem was then,\Nexistence versus non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.78,1:26:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason that's important is\Nbecause it represents
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.78,1:26:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the dilemma of positionality.\NSee, the whole ego arises
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.77,1:26:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,out of positionality.\NAll of duality arises
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.51,1:26:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,out of perception,\Nout of positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.51,1:26:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All of perception\Narises out of positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.21,1:26:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course,\NMiracles talks about
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.21,1:26:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between\Nvision and perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.21,1:26:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception arises\Nout of taking a position.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.56,1:26:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you take\Na position,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.56,1:26:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you've instantly created\Na duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.56,1:26:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You've instantly created\Na perceptual,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.56,1:26:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a way of looking at things\Nthat's going to create
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.49,1:26:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a right and a wrong,\Nand a good and a bad,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.49,1:26:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a good and evil.\NPositionality creates
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.20,1:26:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a world which mankind\Ncannot solve.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.35,1:27:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not solvable.\NThe minute you create
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.91,1:27:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a positionality,\Nyou create
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.00,1:27:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the unsolvable.\NThere's no way
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.00,1:27:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you can...\NThere's the Democrats
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.00,1:27:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in their vote.\NOnce you get a dimple
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.76,1:27:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in reality,\Nyou're screwed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.19,1:27:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Tragically,\Nyou're screwed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.19,1:27:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Pregnant, dimple,\Nor whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.19,1:27:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, positionality\Nwas what I was hit with.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.99,1:27:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't realize it\Nbecause it was going to
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.99,1:27:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,take practically\Na whole lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.99,1:27:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual evolution\Nbefore I returned
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.05,1:27:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to that same\Npositionality
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.18,1:27:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and had to resolve it.\NI had to jump
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.18,1:27:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that paradox,\Nthe paradox
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.18,1:27:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of existence\Nversus non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.18,1:27:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\Nwhen it did,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.40,1:27:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.52,1:27:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,took a leap\Nbecause that was
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.52,1:27:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the great\Nblock.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.52,1:28:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The great block\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.52,1:28:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it represented\Nthe whole
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.52,1:28:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,error\Nof the ego itself
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.52,1:28:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that it\Nthinks that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.64,1:28:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there has to be\Nan opposite
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.64,1:28:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to truth.\NThere has to be
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.64,1:28:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,an opposite\Nto truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.98,1:28:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you take\Na positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.33,1:28:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the ego thinks\Nthat if something
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.33,1:28:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is,\Nthat brings up
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.33,1:28:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the possibility\Nof is not.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.26,1:28:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything\Nthen brings up
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.26,1:28:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,its opposite.\NIt's profound
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.54,1:28:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Npeople
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.54,1:28:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,other than myself\Nfrankly don't
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.54,1:28:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,understand\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.37,1:28:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they think\Nit represents
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.65,1:28:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,true versus\Nfalse.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.73,1:28:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself\Neven thought
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.73,1:28:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so.\NIn trying to explain
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.73,1:28:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it in terms\Nof the world
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.73,1:28:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I came up\Nwith the same
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.73,1:28:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacy\Nthat the world
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.53,1:29:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,does.\NIf there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.43,1:29:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a true\Nthen there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.72,1:29:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.\NIf there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.94,1:29:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,existence\Nthen there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.13,1:29:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.\NIf there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.13,1:29:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,an existence\Nthen there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.62,1:29:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.\NIf there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.62,1:29:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a truth\Nthen there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.72,1:29:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.\NIf there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.42,1:29:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a truth\Nthen there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.21,1:29:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.\NIf there's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.24,1:29:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,an existence\Nthen there must
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.40,1:29:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,be a false.\NIn the past
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.42,1:29:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,there were\Ntwo kinds
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.42,1:29:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of constructions\Nthat have not
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.42,1:29:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not\Nbased on
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.58,1:29:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,unreality.\NSo we said
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.58,1:29:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's commonly\Ntaught
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.61,1:29:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that kinesiology\NSo, when I state truth, then, consciousness recognizes truth, and her arm goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.72,1:30:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say something that is not true, which is different than false, the absence of truth\Nis not falsity, it's just the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.50,1:30:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In the absence of truth, there's no energy to her arm, and her arm goes weak.\NSo, what we're really getting is not true versus false, but true versus not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.37,1:30:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a great addition to a great . . . that is correct.\NOh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.35,1:30:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what this means then, just as I was presented at age three or four, whatever it was, there's\Nonly that which is, there is only existence, there isn't such thing as nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.24,1:31:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonexistence is not a possibility, a possibility would have to be a realizable reality.\NNonexistence by definition is not a realizable reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.51,1:31:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.\NNow, there's an epistemologic realization, it would blow your head right off.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.11,1:31:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the way to understand this then is, reality is what is, what is not is not.\NThere's no point to fear what is not, because if it has no reality, why fear it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.24,1:31:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at, if we run electricity through a wire, we say it's on, and then when there's\Nno electricity, we don't say, well, now there's offness there.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.48,1:31:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth electricity is either there, or it is not there.\NWhen electricity is not there, it doesn't mean that the opposite of electricity is
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.95,1:32:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,now there, something called offness, you understand?\NThis is very profound, this is the greater understanding that all of mankind has ever
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.69,1:32:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,reached.\NIt thinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.74,1:32:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just an offness.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.02,1:32:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we discovered then with kinesiology is that truth makes you go strong, and you\Ngo weak merely in the absence of truth, not in the presence of falsehood, because falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.11,1:32:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,does not exist.\NTruth is either present or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.06,1:32:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NNow, suddenly I understood the first page in A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.75,1:32:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Only that truth is true, nothing else exists, therefore there is nothing to fear.\NAnd I finally got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.05,1:32:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NA long way around.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.70,1:33:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's presentation that the consciousness was at age three or four, existence versus\Nnon-existence, because in that instant I feared that which is not, I feared non-existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.97,1:33:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,scared to death of non-existence.\NBut if I am, it could have been that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.19,1:33:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It could have been that.\NIt could have been that I would not have been.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.19,1:33:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NThe hypothetical possibility of non-existence arose, and with it, fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.93,1:33:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there was the ego reborn in this lifetime, and its fear of non-existence.\NSo, that took care of me at age three or four, and that was the presentation of the dilemma
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.72,1:33:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of this lifetime.\NIt took me another, what, seventy years to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.15,1:33:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.15,1:33:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a very profound, it was a presentation, and it was non-verbal, and there was no way\Nto speak of it to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.03,1:34:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And nothing else of any particular interest happened, except that I was not particularly\Nphysical.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.03,1:34:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I wasn't much into physicality, I like nature, but wrestling and stickball and sticking\Ngreasy fingernails in people's eyes was not my idea of fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.83,1:34:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, other boys sort of enjoyed this physical adversarial kind of amusement, which I was\Nalways very boring.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.90,1:34:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But, other than that, I seemed like a normal boy, and I used to say I graduated at the\Ntop of my class in kindergarten.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.54,1:34:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a straight A in crayons.\NI made that joke up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.54,1:34:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stupid.\NAnyway, you don't want to sound too serious or anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.54,1:34:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, in teenage, I did have a problem in that I'd be sitting in class, and in the\Nminute if I started to think about who I was, think of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.54,1:34:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.\NThink of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.08,1:34:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.\NThink of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.08,1:34:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.\NThink of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.87,1:34:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.\NThink of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.87,1:34:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.\NThink of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.87,1:34:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.\NThink of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.87,1:34:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.\NThink of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.87,1:34:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.\NThink of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.87,1:34:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of I.\NThink of I.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.97,1:34:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought of I, the self would begin, that which the world calls the self, would begin\Nto dissolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.06,1:35:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If there was the self, I would lose track of an individual, discrete entity called I,\Nwhich the world addresses David all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.22,1:35:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I assume that's his name, because that's what they kept calling him then.\NAnd, this would sort of tend to dissolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.31,1:35:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one time I had a paper wrote when I was about 12 or 14.\NI wrote about this in the back of the book, Power Versus Self.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.41,1:35:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a note about the author at the end.\NWell, they probably wanted to know who he is, so I put it in the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.41,1:35:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, later people said, you should put that at the front.\NWell, anyway, I put it in the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.66,1:35:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, about 12 or 14, somewhere in that, I had this paper wrote, and in the middle\Nof a blizzard, it was very dark and I got lost in this blizzard, it was many miles from
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.66,1:35:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,home, and I was free, you know, I actually sort of freed from death, and so I dug into\Na big snowbank there in Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.94,1:35:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In Wisconsin, the snow is very high.\NSo, I dug into a big snowbank there, a big one.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.01,1:36:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and the snow was very high on Saturday night, 12 feet high or 15 feet high.\NSo anyway, I dug through the, into the snow and got into this hole out of the wind.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.92,1:36:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the wind was fierce.\NIt was about 20 blow or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.64,1:36:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I snuggled in there, and very soon, very quickly,\Na profound sense of relaxation and peace came on me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.98,1:36:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really incredible.\NIt was the infinite, exquisite sensation of gentleness.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.46,1:36:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like exquisite love just took me over in this golden presence.\NAnd to this day, I wish I'd stayed there anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.98,1:36:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, all time disappeared.\NThat which, this golden, infinite presence of exquisite love,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.86,1:36:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,melting, just melted away any personal.\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.62,1:36:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no self, which dissolved.\NThere wasn't any personal self.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.94,1:37:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There was just this infinite presence.\NNot different than that which I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.20,1:37:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw that which I am is before all universes\Nand will exist long after all universes have come and gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.70,1:37:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond all time, beyond all dimension, beyond all universes, beyond all description.\NThis infinite presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.12,1:37:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there I stayed for some eons or so.\NAnd the next thing I knew, my father was shaking my knee to come on our Model A Ford,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.38,1:37:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,29 Model A Ford, and located the body there in the hole and retraced the paper route.\NAnd then, anyway, he was quite shaken by all this.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.96,1:37:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, father reaches in and grabs the knee.\NAnd I really was extremely reluctant to resume this physicality.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.52,1:37:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But I got that he believes in death.\NI could see that he would think that if this body,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.65,1:38:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,if this body didn't start to move again, that it was dead, and that he, that I had died.\NAnd this would bring profound grief.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.41,1:38:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's the idea that it's absurd, you know.\NBut anyway, in his state, it seemed like a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.65,1:38:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In my state, it was an absurdity.\NAbsurdity.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.89,1:38:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But I saw that he couldn't see my state.\NSo, for the sake of love, then, I re-energized this body.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.46,1:38:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was probably a mistake.\NSo, this happened on several occasions throughout my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.96,1:38:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this happened on several occasions throughout my life.\NSo, this happened on several occasions throughout my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.32,1:38:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it happened another time under similar conditions.\NAnd I was doing rebirthing, and the breathing stopped.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.76,1:38:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the same space, I went back into being that way, which I am.\NAnd there was no necessity to breathe again.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.17,1:38:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't see any reason to breathe.\NBut I didn't seem to need to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.05,1:38:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't interested in breathing.\NBut the rebirther took quite a concerned interest in whether I breathed or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.44,1:39:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughter\NHe was teaching me this.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.09,1:39:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He was teaching me this technique, you know.\NAnd anyway, I loved him.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.84,1:39:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, telepathically, I'm getting from him, breathe, Dave, you know.\NAnd I got his position.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.36,1:39:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was his first patient, his first rebirther.\NHe was a rebirther.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.68,1:39:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He had just come back from the place that grew green pig vegetables there by the sea.\NI forget where.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.28,1:39:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Benhorn, yes.\NWell, he had taken the course of miracles to Benhorn.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.02,1:39:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He had taken the course of miracles.\NHe was now into rebirthing.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.51,1:39:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Dave, I've got to show you this.\NHe takes me on this rebirthing trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.22,1:39:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.\NAnyway, there was no desire.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.72,1:39:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could see the same thing happening all over again.\NHere I am in this incredible space.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.88,1:39:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's this idiot thinking that I'm going to die if I don't breathe again.\NAnd I see that the whole world is going to believe, believe that he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.28,1:39:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Dave died.\NSo, and it's going to be on his head.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.16,1:40:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he's looking at me, you know, projecting the position I'm going to leave him if I don't breathe again.\NI said, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.62,1:40:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, again, I made the same fatal mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.91,1:40:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Laughter\NAnd out of love resumed it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.95,1:40:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And, but then the more interesting things that happened were perhaps in spiritual work, you know,\NI would belong to the first Zen Institute.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.93,1:40:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was a psychiatric consultant to the Zen monastery and the Episcopal Diocese and the Catholic Diocese and the Catholic nuns.\NAnd so my spiritual experience was sort of used in a way to differentiate.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.51,1:40:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, abnormal religious states from legitimate states.\NAnd, uh, that was before we had a kinesiology or any way to test such things.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.84,1:41:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, at one time I, um, was in a profound state of illness.\NAnd, uh, I went into this profound state of illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.53,1:41:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, one time I went out of body.\NI might as well relate all these experiences.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.35,1:41:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a difference between near death and out of body.\NAnd I just want to make that clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.69,1:41:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Near, near death was the golden, uh, exquisite.\NWhen you calibrate the low.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.15,1:41:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness of that, uh, uh, field of energy, uh, you get it's quite a high, high field.\NAnd, uh, the person's consciousness is not the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.19,1:41:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Once, a near death experience, you're different.\NUh, you see the fear of death disappears altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.13,1:41:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I never had the fear of death from age 12 on.\NThe fear of death disappears and very often their whole life is somewhat transformed.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.58,1:41:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of body is, is different.\NOut of body, uh, happened one time when I was very physically sick.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.08,1:42:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, suddenly found myself in mid-air, six feet over this physical body, looking down at the bed, and there was Dave in this bed.\NHa, ha, he was a mess, I'll tell ya.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.60,1:42:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at him, I thought, God, he should be leaving this world soon.\NAnd, uh, but this was totally different.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.98,1:42:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no golden light.\NThere was no exquisite presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.86,1:42:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was, um, weightlessness and, uh, thought, feeling, uh, and, uh, capacity to see and hear went with, uh, spirit body.\NWent with the etheric.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.93,1:42:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I am up in space, and I look, here's this body, it's almost exactly like this one, except it's, uh, almost like invisible.\NYou can see right, right through it, it had no weight.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.43,1:42:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And a slight thought would move it anywhere in space, it was like weightless.\NAnd I remember looking down and seeing the physical body laying in the bed, and, uh, later that was interesting because I realized that, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.90,1:42:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the quality of hearing, thinking, feeling, et cetera, goes with the etheric body.\NIt doesn't go with the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.83,1:42:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the illusion is, uh,\Nthat it's happening through the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.33,1:43:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you can hear without the body's ears, and you can see without the body's eyes.\NBecause they were laying there in the bed, and I was up there seeing and hearing.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.83,1:43:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, if you calibrate the level of consciousness of the entity before and after this experience, it's the same.\NSo the difference between out-of-body is that you're the same person, it's just that your etheric and physical are separated.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.74,1:43:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And the near-death is quite a different, more profound, transformative experience.\NUh, then, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.50,1:43:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to clarify, because I saw a TV documentary on it,\Nand it confused the two states,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.50,1:43:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,treated near-death and out-of-body as though they were the same thing.\NAnd they're quite a bit different, quite a bit different.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.50,1:43:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's, let's calibrate, what was the level of, uh, snowbank experience, you know?\NDo we have permission to calibrate that resist?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.34,1:43:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was over 600 resist.\NIt was over 700 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.37,1:43:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 750 resist.\NIt was 800 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.37,1:43:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 900 resist.\NIt was over 900 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.37,1:43:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.\NOh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.72,1:43:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, uh,\Num,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.23,1:44:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the Divine Presence was actually the Divine Presence,\Nand, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.33,1:44:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought it was God, but didn't want to say anything.\NSee, you can calibrate where, what was that experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.33,1:44:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that you had or other people had.\NI mean, you can go back through history, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.33,1:44:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual experiences of saints and various people.\NWhat's real, what's not real.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.33,1:44:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the level of calibration of that?\NI mean, you begin to get a feeling for the entire spiritual dimension
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.42,1:44:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of what's real, and where does it fit into the overall reality,\Nand many supposed dilemmas result in self.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.42,1:44:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, at the bottom, uh, then, uh, at a certain age,\NI suddenly became, well, I was brought up Episcopal,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.54,1:44:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was very religious, and, uh, I was a boy soprano,\Nuh, boy soprano with, uh, a choir and a full orchestra
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.82,1:44:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and a cathedral, and I sang the Obligato to Panis Angelicus.\NOh, it brought tears to the eyes of me
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.02,1:45:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody in the room.\NHere's a soprano boy, Obligato, with his voice coming out of
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.02,1:45:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where.\NAnd, uh, this whole floor, I mean, it was really a great moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.02,1:45:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So religion, you know, used to just lift me up,\Nthe sheer aesthetics of it, the sheer beauty of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.02,1:45:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the sheer beauty and joy of the cathedral,\Nuh, and the entire pageantry of it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.02,1:45:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an exquisite experience.\NUh, well, anyway, so, then one time,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.01,1:45:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking at, uh, the suffering of man,\Nmankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.01,1:45:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, all of a sudden, um, I came into the awareness\Nof the totality of the suffering of all of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.37,1:45:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,like I saw all of it.\NIt was beyond all dimension, all capacity to describe.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.30,1:45:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of the suffering of mankind throughout all of time\Nwas so profound that in that instant I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.26,1:46:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, um, any God that could allow this possibility\Ncould not be God to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.96,1:46:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the fire.\NI'm a profound atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.47,1:46:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A dedicated atheist.\NNot a fool around atheists.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.66,1:46:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was as serious about atheism as I had been about religion, you see.\NAnd I went to a Jesuit university.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.70,1:46:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I am with this profound atheist at a Jesuit university.\NI'm getting straight A in theology and Thomas Aquinas
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.70,1:46:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and all this.\NAnd in myself, I'm an atheist, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.95,1:46:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, uh, that was the position I took.\NOne that a great part of mankind takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.04,1:46:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand it because I experienced the very essence of it.\NWithout understanding karma, without understanding the true nature of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.29,1:46:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody with any brain really ought to be an atheist.\NIf you think God is the cause of all that occurs in this universe, in this world,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.41,1:47:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and you still believe in him, then you must be pretty depraved.\NSo, the honest arguments for the existence of God
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.75,1:47:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,have made atheists and many an honest man.\NAnd I was one of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.75,1:47:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How could an all-merciful, all-loving, all-beneficial, beneficial God\Nallow that degree of negativity and suffering of all mankind?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.91,1:47:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point, I became an atheist.\NAnd I was a very serious atheist, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.18,1:47:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I really took it seriously.\NI loved religious discussions and theological discussions, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.79,1:47:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was really good at it, too.\NYou know, I could really, like, take a snack, take that.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.79,1:47:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really good at it.\NSo, anyway, I was out to destroy the false gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.79,1:47:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize they were false gods.\NBut it was the false concept, conceptions of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.79,1:47:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that I had taken issue with.\NAnd as it turned out, certainly so.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.98,1:48:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, the misconceptions of God is what anybody\Nwith any real profound spiritual sense cannot buy,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.14,1:48:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,unless there's profound negative depictions of God.\NSo, anyway, I was a profound atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.82,1:48:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And after some years went by,\NI then developed some other illnesses.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.82,1:48:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And at one time, I hit a state of profound spiritual blackness,\Nprofound depth, spiritual depths.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.58,1:48:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, the pits of hell, in a way.\NPits of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.16,1:48:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Despair and blackness beyond all description.\NAnd in this black despair, it was really sort of the pits of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.25,1:48:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the upper parts of hell are torture and the devil\Nand all that kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.25,1:48:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But those are just the upper realms.\NAnd the bottom realms are those of profound spiritual desolation,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.72,1:49:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,cut off from all light, you might say.\NAnd in that state, here I'm an atheist, a devoted atheist,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.19,1:49:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, and I thought, I'm probably going to die.\NI thought, I'm about to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.80,1:49:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, before I do, I mean, what if I'm wrong?\NIn a couple of minutes, this could be tacky.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.80,1:49:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you could be on the other side.\NOkay, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.80,1:49:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A few errors we ought to look into here, you know.\NI said, well, if there is a God, I ask him to help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.44,1:49:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, I don't remember anything.\NI don't remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.63,1:49:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I came to, when I came to some days later,\Nor whenever it was, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.98,1:49:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,everything had been transformed.\NAll of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.98,1:49:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My experience of existence, of my own existence.\NEverything was totally transformed.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.94,1:49:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only a brilliant...\NThe divinity of all things shines forth equally
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.39,1:50:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,as the essence of all things being what they are.\NThe exquisite beauty of the infinite presence is overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.39,1:50:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mind, what the world calls the mind, it stopped.\NNo thought, no thought possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.35,1:50:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind still doesn't think.\NIt doesn't think at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.48,1:50:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning it wasn't thinking about anything.\NIt was wandering around, I don't know what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.48,1:50:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the mind just came to a stunning stop.\NAnd nor would there be any, even the slightest,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.61,1:50:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,possibility of having a thought in that presence.\NThe presence is of such infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.67,1:50:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Power is so infinite.\NIt's like the intrinsic power that holds everything together.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.08,1:50:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that holds this room together.\NPower.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.08,1:50:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And this infinite power is also exquisitely gentle.\NAnd closer, closer than what one thinks of as one's self.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.72,1:50:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What you think of as yourself.\NIs really quite distant from what you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.98,1:51:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you, the realization of the self with a capital S\Nis more profoundly one's home.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.98,1:51:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of one's existence.\NWhere one really lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.07,1:51:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Than what had been thought of as one's self.\NSo this infinite presence then,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.42,1:51:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which took the place of all that had prior existence,\NJohn Dowdall thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.48,1:51:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,John Dowdall thought of an individual separate self,\Nor an I.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.48,1:51:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The world called data on earth to figure out what they were talking about at the time.\NWhen it first happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.72,1:51:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There was quite a difficulty in pronouns.\NAnd the people were always talking to this body.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.72,1:51:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And it would mystify me.\NWhy the hell are they talking to that body?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.72,1:51:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not even there.\NI mean, why are they?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.72,1:51:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I realized that they assumed that this body is me.\NOh wow, I got that.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.20,1:51:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was quite a while, some years in fact,\Nthat I could figure out how to really function within the world again.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.20,1:52:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the world didn't, the world, the mind didn't say anything.\NPeople spoke with things that seemed to have no reality or relevance whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:04.58,1:52:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a split second of translation.\NI see the person's mouth speaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.29,1:52:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The words impinge on the ear, but they don't have any meaning.\NAnd the Holy Spirit translates that into an understanding of what is being said.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.61,1:52:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Or I'll say to somebody, what are they saying?\NAnd that gives me the moment I need.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:27.64,1:52:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,To interpret what is happening within the world of form.\NSo there was some years of trying to live within the world of form.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.98,1:52:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how I left New York City and the big practice I had there and all.\NAnd I went out to a small town.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.30,1:52:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And for about ten years I had nothing to do with the world.\NI just got used to the state and how to regain functioning within it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.34,1:53:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was quite a remarkable thing.\NThen there were various sensations along the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.42,1:53:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In the eye of the eye, I think I wrote about them.\NPeople do a lot of spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.55,1:53:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They really need others to compare their experience with.\NBecause there isn't all that many people out there to talk to about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.55,1:53:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, well, maybe a lot of the things I consider irrelevant maybe are not irrelevant.\NMaybe I should write about them.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:17.55,1:53:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should...\NThere was a period when the kundalini energy was running up my spine.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.68,1:53:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It was exquisite.\NI mean, it wasn't happening to anybody else.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.68,1:53:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I could run around and say, hey, there's something running up your spine.\NIt feels exquisite, like a little great orgasm going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.68,1:53:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All the time in your brain.\NWhoa, Doc, you really tipped over, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.68,1:53:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Seen too many crazies, huh?\NSo anyway, yeah, it was exquisite energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.68,1:53:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I forget what I was doing at the time.\NBut anyway, some spiritual practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.68,1:53:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It can happen to almost any spiritual practice.\NYou do the Course in Miracles and you have all kinds of incredible experiences.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.74,1:53:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this energy is running up the spine and up my back.\NAnd it's pouring into my brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.74,1:54:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's exquisite, exquisite all the time.\NExquisitely pleasurable.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.35,1:54:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Just, oh.\NAnd if I would think of the left side of my brain, it would sort of like go into the left side of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.51,1:54:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If I think of the right side of the brain, it would go into the right side of the brain.\NOh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.51,1:54:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this exquisite energy went on for years.\NAnd then it would come down this way and sort of go out through the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.86,1:54:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd be driving somewhere and all of a sudden this energy would pour out down the road or something.\NAnd a very exquisite sensation.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:32.25,1:54:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd say, well, I don't know what.\NAnd this energy would go down the highway some miles ahead of where I was.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:40.25,1:54:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I turned the bend, there was an accident.\NThe car is upside down and the wheels are still turning.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:46.28,1:54:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And this energy is pouring into the car.\NAnd I got that there was no need to stop physically.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:53.72,1:54:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no need for physical assistance on my part.\NThis energy seemed to be handling everything that needed to be handled.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.72,1:55:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then as I go down the road, it stopped again.\NAnd I'm going down the highway again.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:06.91,1:55:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden it started again.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:10.04,1:55:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going around the next bend a couple of miles ahead.\NExquisite.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.04,1:55:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Just pouring out into this like a radiance.\NAnd I come around the bend and there, my God, there's another accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:21.65,1:55:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This time the emergency vehicles are on the way.\NAnd the lights are flashing.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:27.65,1:55:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming down the highway.\NAnd this energy poured into the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.65,1:55:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And this energy poured into the people in that wreck.\NAnd did the same thing again.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.81,1:55:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So this peculiar phenomena would occur.\NAnd various paranormal, what the world calls paranormal phenomena would happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.38,1:55:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Sanskrit, it's called the various cities.\NYou know, the S-I-B-D-H-I-S.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.38,1:55:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're warned not to get trapped by them or enamored of them.\NFirst of all, they happen as a result of the presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.69,1:56:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They have nothing to do with you.\NThis divine presence did all these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.69,1:56:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This presence would answer people's questions.\NIt would phrase responses that the body would verbalize to the person's question.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:13.78,1:56:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And it would be amazing, I think.\NI said, wow, that's pretty neat.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:17.78,1:56:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there was clairvoyance.\NThere was this envision.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:25.84,1:56:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There was, what do you call it, psychometry.\NWhere you pick up something, you know, whose book this is.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:30.84,1:56:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see who that person is.\NAnd you've got everything about that person.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:35.35,1:56:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Just from touching it.\NAnd that would occur automatically.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.35,1:56:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And all those things came and went.\NYou know, they would last for, oh, four or five years.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:45.28,1:56:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Electronic things would fix themselves.\NAnd somebody would come over to repair a 100-amp amplifier.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:54.53,1:57:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd look at it and I'd say, I don't know, it looks okay to me.\NAnd instantly the thing would go off.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.23,1:57:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the guy looks at it and he says, whoa.\NWhat did you do there?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.23,1:57:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I didn't do it.\NI said, there's some kind of presence that does these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:09.55,1:57:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, it all started from reading The Chorus of Miracles.\NHe said, gee, I want that book.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.55,1:57:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I had exactly one copy left, so I gave it to him.\NHe says, well, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:20.55,1:57:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And he left and tears me to the surface for you.\NAnd he only came over to get The Chorus of Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:26.55,1:57:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, you know, God sent him over.\NHe came over to get The Chorus of Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.90,1:57:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I never saw him again.\NBut those things were, they lasted for, I don't know, five or six years, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.80,1:57:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Some years it was, I hadn't even been in the same, that state before.\NAnd people would say, we're running out of gas.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:44.86,1:57:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd say, oh, there's a Saccone station a mile or two down the road.\NI could see it in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.47,1:57:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all exactly where it is, you know, around the trees there.\NAnd so this phenomenon would occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.54,1:58:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes, the paranormal does have a certain reality.\NYeah, yeah, it does exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.54,1:58:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we notice about Scripture is it's going to exist.\NBut what we don't notice about Scripture is that Scripture says, it doesn't say the supernatural doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:07.54,1:58:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It just says, don't go there.\NDon't go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:10.54,1:58:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause you get caught in the astral realms, that's why.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:13.54,1:58:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You get caught in the astral realms.\NAnd so much of what people think is spiritual, especially in New Age groups,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:19.57,1:58:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that don't have being on the earth, is, you know, endless preoccupation with astral realms.\NThere are endless astral realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:29.69,1:58:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There are heavens upon heavens, and there's hierarchies,\Nand there's masters and gurus,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:34.72,1:58:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and followers,\Nand mystical carryings on,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:38.88,1:58:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and people with the colored rays,\Nand people with the light beams,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:41.88,1:58:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and people with the...\NAh, the world's full of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:47.30,1:58:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the astral domains is not the same as the spiritual reality.\NSo I want to make that clear,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:54.42,1:59:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because a lot of seekers get pulled into early astral domains.\NIf you're going to listen to somebody channeling master so-and-so,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:05.64,1:59:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you better calibrate the energy of master so-and-so on the other side.\NVery, very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:10.38,1:59:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because very often master so-and-so is in the control,\Nin the control,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:14.38,1:59:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrates less than 200.\NHis only desire is to control people out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.38,1:59:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got them sitting out there waiting for UFOs to land and save them in the middle of the desert\Nand all kinds of crazy crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:27.38,1:59:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are just demons that get a kick out of scaring people,\Nespecially if they think they have some kind of...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:32.38,1:59:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They're on some spiritual trick, you know.\NWell, if you're a demon,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:35.38,1:59:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't you just love to twist people's noses around a spiritual trick\Nand say,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.38,1:59:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,take that,\Nsit out in the middle of the desert and starve to death?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:42.38,1:59:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They do, you know.\NThey'll go out in the desert and wait for God to show up.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:46.89,1:59:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of strange things.\NSo one reason to calibrate things is
Dialogue: 0,1:59:51.46,1:59:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not that a channeled teaching is necessarily negative.\NIt may well be positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:59.50,2:00:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know who is it,\Nyou know, what is the level of truth of the consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:03.50,2:00:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because many people go into,\Nooh, ah, it's all master.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:06.50,2:00:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Baba, ding dong.\NAnd, you know, you go,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:09.50,2:00:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the energy of Master Ding Dong?\NI'm going to think it was very Chinese Baba right now.
